Opera House Cup ‘23

Epic day on the water for the 51St OHC aboard RANGER!

The Nantucket Opera House Cup Regatta stands as a true gem among sailing events, renowned for its blend of maritime heritage, competitive spirit, and scenic beauty. Set against the backdrop of the charming island of Nantucket, this regatta holds a special place in the sailing world.

The event captures the essence of classic yacht racing, drawing sailing enthusiasts from all corners to witness a spectacular display of elegance and craftsmanship. With a focus on preserving the rich maritime traditions, the Nantucket Opera House Cup Regatta showcases an array of meticulously maintained vintage and classic yachts. These graceful vessels, ranging from traditional wooden sailboats to sleek sloops, evoke the nostalgia of a bygone era while still engaging in spirited competition.

Spectators and participants alike are treated to a unique experience where history and sport converge. The regatta's route takes sailors through the sparkling waters surrounding Nantucket, offering breathtaking views of the island's coastline and the open sea. The sense of camaraderie among sailors and the vibrant atmosphere ashore add to the event's allure.

Organized with great attention to detail, the Nantucket Opera House Cup Regatta is not only a showcase of maritime craftsmanship but also a celebration of community and seafaring culture. Its reputation as one of the premier classic yacht races underscores the event's significance and appeal to those who appreciate the artistry, elegance, and competitive spirit that define the world of sailing.

Step into the unique world of 84 Mercer, a stunning 3-bed, 3.5-bath residence blending historical elegance with modern luxury. The full-floor loft showcases meticulously restored iron columns and wood beams, harmonizing with contemporary elements like steel, stone, and glass finishes. A private keyed elevator entrance leads to a grand space with 14’ high ceilings and abundant natural light from oversized Western windows. The open-concept layout seamlessly integrates living, kitchen, and dining areas for versatile entertaining.

The chef’s kitchen features top-of-the-line appliances, a hidden pantry, and a stylish island. A lofted media space offers a cozy movie night spot and connects to the expansive primary suite with a uniquely designed contemporary bathroom. Secondary bedrooms, each with built-in storage and en suite baths, complement the home office and integrated Creston lighting, shades, and Sonos sound system.

Nestled in Soho’s historic district, 84 Mercer is part of the esteemed 515 Broadway Corp. Built-in 1884, it transformed into a residential cooperative in 1978, featuring a mesmerizing Queen Anne façade. This pet-friendly coop provides secure elevator access and subletting privileges. Located in the heart of Soho, between Spring and Broome Streets, 84 Mercer is a crown jewel of downtown living, surrounded by fine dining, vibrant nightlife, and unparalleled shopping experiences.
